{
  "texts": [
    "10].For all simulations we consider the time interval.",
    "The small positive values of R 0, R * 0 are used simply so that all initial conditions are positive and theorem 3.1 holds.",
    "In this manner, at the outset, roughly half the population is infected and half the population is noncompliant.",
    "All of these choices are synthetic, and are not meant to reflect any specific real-world scenario, but rather to demonstrate the behavior of the model.",
    "The remaining parameters are the disease infectivity rate (β), the portion of newly introduced population which is noncompliant (ξ), the infectivity and recovery rates for noncompliance (µ and ν respectively), the levels of uncertainty in the infectivity rates for the disease (σ β) and noncompliance (σ µ)."
  ]
}